The '''Sulawesi nightjar''' ('''''Caprimulgus celebensis''''') is a species of [[nightjar]] in the family [[Caprimulgidae]]. It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Indonesia]], where it occurs on [[Sulawesi]] and the [[Sula Islands]]. Its natural [[habitat]]s are subtropical or tropical moist lowland [[forest]]s and subtropical or tropical mangrove forests.

